<h3 id="conditional">Conditionally revealing content</h3>

<p>Reveal additional input fields, depending on the context.<br />A left border is applied to emphasise this supporting information.</p>


<p>Wrap the element you wish to hide until revealed with the following code:</p>

<pre><code class="pattern-source html"><div class="conditional-content" aria-hidden="true">
	[Your hidden input]
</div></code></pre>

<p>Then use the following JavaScript code:</p>
<pre><code class="pattern-source js">$(document).ready(function() {
    $('input.input-name').change(
        function() {
            var val = $(this).val();

            if(val === "option-value") {
                $(".conditional-content").show();
            }
            else if(val !== "option-value") {
                $(".conditional-content").hide();
            }
        }   
    );  
});</code></pre>
<ul>
	<li>Replace <code>input-name</code> with the class of the input you wish to affect.</li>
	<li>Replace <code>option-value</code> with the option you wish to show conditional content on.<br />(In the below example, this value is set to 'other').</li>
</ul>



